+### Motivation
+- Make navigation easier by adding a visible back arrow that returns the user to the previous page or a sensible fallback URL when history is not available.
+
+### Description
+- Add a reusable `goBack` helper in `public/assets/js/app.js` that uses `window.history.back()` with an optional fallback URL.
+- Add shared styles `.topbar-left`, `.btn.back-button` and `.back-floating` in `public/assets/css/theme.css` to style inline and floating back controls.
+- Insert back arrow controls into the global header (`app/views/partials/header.php`) and add back buttons to standalone pages `login.php`, `install/index.php`, `patient_card.php`, `patient_card_pdf.php`, and the print pages `print_visit.php`, `print_rx.php`, `print_referral.php`, `print_consent.php`, and `print_sick_letter.php`, using `goBack()` with appropriate fallback URLs.
+- Include the app script where needed by adding `<script src="<?= e(url('/public/assets/js/app.js')) ?>"></script>` to pages that previously didn’t load the helper script.
+
+### Testing
+- No automated tests were run.
